Class SeqNFunction

Direct Known Subclasses:
Seq2Function, Seq3Function
public class SeqNFunction
extends Node

A function node which provides the facility to sequence a specific number of instructions, specified at construction. Each of the instructions may be any other function or terminal node with a Void return type. This is the same function that Koza calls progN in his work.

getReturnType

public java.lang.Class<?> getReturnType(java.lang.Class<?>... inputTypes)
Returns this function node's return type for the given child input types. If there is the correct number of inputs of Void type, then the return type of this function is Void. Otherwise this method will return null to indicate that the inputs are invalid.

Overrides:
getReturnType in class Node
Parameters:
inputTypes - the set of input data-types for which to get the return type.
Returns:
The Void class or null if the input type is invalid.
